            <bug_when>2011-08-05 11:38:26 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The qx* locators will throw errors if e.g. a qooxdoo object was not found, doesn&#39;t have a DOM element etc. This can cause problems with commands such as isElementPresent, forcing test developers to always wrap them in try... catch blocks. Just like Selenium&#39;s built-ine locators, qxh* locators should simply return null if they can&#39;t find their target for whatever reason.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
